text:
Caribbean Dream Cruise Plc.
Sun Avenue 10
London, W6 7HB, United Kingdom
10. January 2023
Guarantee No. 230BGI2301287 for Warranty Obligations
Dear Sirs,
We have been informed that a contract, hereinafter "Underlying Relationship", has been
concluded between you and Great Boats Shipyard GmbH & Co. KG, Planken Str. 10, 20095
Hamburg, hereinafter "Applicant", on 10.01.2023 under ref. No. 10234598 for the delivery of
new cruise ship named "Holiday Dream" as stated in the contract with ref. No. 10234598 at a
total price of USD 350.000.000,00 and that the Underlying Relationship stipulates that a
Guarantee for Warranty Obligations be issued in the amount of 90% of the total price.
This being premised, we, Cruise Bank AG, Rostock hereby irrevocably undertake to pay you
without delay on your first written demand for payment an amount up to
USD 315.000.000,00
(in words: US-Dollar three hundred fifteen million 00/100)
upon presentation of your complying demand in paper form, supported by your written
statement, whether in the demand itself or in a separate signed document accompanying or
identifying the demand, indicating in what respect the Applicant is in breach of its obligations
under the Underlying Relationship.
This Guarantee is valid from 10th January 2023 and shall expire on 10th January 2025 and is
conditional upon claim(s) being made and received by us not later than three (3) months from
the Expiry Date. Thereafter, our liability hereunder shall automatically cease and this
Guarantee shall become null and void.)
This guarantee is only transferable and the proceeds to which you may be or may become
entitled under this guarantee are only assignable with our prior written consent.
This guarantee is subject to the Uniform Rules for Demand Guarantees, ICC Publication No.
758 (URDG), and German law.
Cruise Bank AG
